# OpenHarness repository context

This repo defines the **OpenHarness wire protocol** (Shell ↔ Harness Engine). It is **not** a vendor-specific Engine product binary.

## Sources of truth

- **Normative:** `docs/PROTOCOL.md` (English, authoritative) and `docs/PROTOCOL.zh.md` (Chinese mirror).
- **Schema:** `schema/openharness-v1.draft.json` — validate request vs response messages **separately** (root is `oneOf`).
- **Scope / layering:** `docs/SCOPE.md`, `docs/OVERVIEW.md` (informative).

## Implementing adapters or examples (humans + AI)

- Read **`docs/guides/AI_INTEGRATION.md`** — checklists, anti-patterns, and a copy-paste prompt block.
- Use **`examples/minimal/`** and **`examples/im-cli/`** as golden JSON references; do not invent fields that contradict PROTOCOL.
- For IM/bot Shell responsibilities (mapping platform IDs into `context`, etc.), see **`docs/profiles/im-bot-shell.md`**.
- **§11 unknown `action_type`:** never execute side effects for unknown directive types.
- **Attachments:** references only in the body — no large base64 payloads (`PROTOCOL` §9.1).
- **Capabilities:** handle `capability_denials` / `supported_capabilities`; avoid silent half-features.

## When changing the wire format

Update in one PR: `docs/PROTOCOL.md`, `docs/PROTOCOL.zh.md`, `schema/openharness-v1.draft.json`, and **relevant `examples/*.json`** so fixtures stay valid.
